I'll start by executing the network_fetcher tool to retrieve data from the API endpoint as the first step in the workflow.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            I'll now execute the data_processing_parser to process the data retrieved by the network_fetcher. Since we're working with the default parameters, I'll use the standard configuration.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll proceed with the final step in the workflow by executing the data_processing_validator to validate the parsed data. I'll use the default schema and parameters.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {},
  "data": {},
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
